title: Gonzo: The Life and Work of Dr. Hunter S. Thompson--vikingsfreak
description:
AVI Files


Gonzo: The Life and Work of Dr. Hunter S. Thompson is a 2008 documentary film directed by Alex Gibney. It details Hunter S. Thompson's landmark writings on music and politics.[1] Friends and family (including Tom Wolfe and Ralph Steadman) help describe the mythos of Hunter and his adventures.

The film premiered on January 20 in the Documentary Competition at the 2008 Sundance Film Festival.[1] It was released in theaters in the U.S. on July 4, 2008, and on DVD on November 18, 2008.[2]
